Challenge Description

The challenge presents a simple HTML page that discusses "include directives" in programming. The page references external CSS and JavaScript files, with the hint: "Is there more code than what the inspector initially shows?"
Initial Analysis

The HTML file contains:

    Basic structure with <head> and <body>

    Link to style.css

    Script reference to script.js

    A button that calls a greetings() function

Step-by-Step Solution
1. View Page Source

First, examine the HTML source:
html

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
    <title>On Includes</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <script src="script.js"></script>
    <button type="button" onclick="greetings();">Say hello</button>
  </body>
</html>

2. Check External JavaScript File

Navigate to /script.js to examine the JavaScript code:
javascript

function greetings()
{
    // Function to display time-appropriate greeting
    let date_time = new Date();
    let hours = date_time.getHours();
    // ... greeting logic ...
    alert(greetings + ", " + date_time);
}

// Hidden flag parts in console output and comments
console.log("picoCTF{1nclu51v17y_1of2_");
//  f7w_2of2_df589022}

Discovery:

    First flag part in console.log() statement

    Second flag part in a JavaScript comment

3. Check External CSS File

Navigate to /style.css to examine the stylesheet:
css

body {
  font-family: "Comic Sans MS", "Comic Sans", cursive;
  background-color: teal;
  /* ... other styles ... */
}

/* 7d5e6f8b} */  /* Potential red herring or alternate flag part */

4. Check Browser Console

Open browser developer tools (F12) and view the Console tab to see:
text

picoCTF{1nclu51v17y_1of2_

5. Assemble the Flag

Combine the discovered parts:

    From console.log(): picoCTF{1nclu51v17y_1of2_

    From JavaScript comment: f7w_2of2_df589022}
